reviews.review: It is a good movie by itself, it did a good job in closing all the plots that where left hanging from the previous 2 films. Although it felt a little rushed, with no time to rest, just a succession of fast scenes.
The Rise of Skywalker was very good.  But it could have been better if The Last Jedi had not derailed the story arch.

JJ worked with what he was given. He counters Rian Johnsons antics and puts the story back on its tracks. He then ties it off and ends it with fans having a full heart and remembering their childhood. Thank you JJ for saving the day!

If you're looking for a movie to turn your brain off to and watch large action set pieces and good acting, then you'd probably enjoy this movie. Otherwise, if you care about star wars lore, themes, or just good story telling in general this movie is better left forgotten

Filled with nonsensical plot contrivances and some questionable if not straight up poor character writing, this movie seems more like a bad dungeon master trying to captivate their players with plot twist after plot twist that are doubled back on and legacy characters than a decent movie.

All in all, if you want to be entertained, go see it, if you want to be satisfied with a movie, it's better to look elsewhere

Great movie! Kept me guessing throughout the movie.  Many things brought back memories of my viewing of the first star wars.  Luke, Leah, Han, were so young then but now mature each with a depth of being that makes one feel that they have known all of them for decades.
A lot of action. However story had to many holes. Patch worked.
While its nits can be picked to death as much as 'Last Jedi', the overall result is a movie that feels like a Star Wars movie, with acting that is probably the best in the series.
This is my favorite movie of all time. It gave me everything I wanted. I could watch it every day and enjoy it the same every time. It is perfect. I'd give my life for Ben Solo
Was somewhat disappointed with the 2 previous movies, but as a lifelong Star Wars fan, this one was satisfying.

Very good ending to the Saga. Nice blend of modern culture and good ole' Star Wars. Unlike The Last Jedi, Rise of Skywalker is a more enjoyable, and in terms of the Star Wars fanatic inside me, it left me content. Of course, there were still some questions I had, but none major to the story line. In my opinion, it's the best out of the trilogy Disney has made. I don't feel it's fair to compare it to Rogue One or Solo because those two are a lot more straightforward whereas Rise of Skywalker is A LOT to take in. Of course everyone has their own opinions and this is mine, some other fanatics don't like the movie, but personally, I thought it was great.
